Nike Popoola Heritage Bank Plc has commended health workers globally for their selfless sacrifice and bravery in the fight against the coronavirus pandemic. A statement said it joined the World Health Organisation in the celebration of ‘World Health Workers Week.’ The bank stated that the event was an annual commemoration of health workers but this year’s was scheduled to honour health workers during the 8th annual World Health Worker Week. It stated that the theme of this year’s celebration was, ‘Leaders on the line,’ which according to the WHO highlighted the need to provide greater leadership opportunities for frontline health workers—particularly women health workers, who made up more than 70 per cent of the global health workforce. “This theme emphasises how health workers often put themselves on the line, often at great personal risk to themselves and their families, to save and improve lives,” it stated. Commending the health practitioners worldwide, the Managing Director/Chief Executive Officer, Heritage Bank Plc, Ifie Sekibo, stated that the COVID-19 pandemic had shown the world their heroic efforts on the front line made every day to keep their respective communities and the world safe and healthy. Copyright PUNCH.
